          <div class="meal-card-title">3 Meals · Real Food · No Supplements</div>
          <div class="meal-card-foods">Breakfast + Lunch + Dinner</div>
        </div>
        <div class="meal-card-protein">
          <div class="protein-num">100</div>
          <div class="protein-unit">grams</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Notice what's not on that list: protein bars, multiple shakes, specialty foods, or eating every two hours. Just three real meals, each anchored by a solid protein source. That's all 100g requires.</p>

    <h2>The Foods That Make 100g Easy</h2>

    <p>Getting to 100 grams consistently comes down to knowing which foods carry the most protein per serving. These are the ones to build your meals around.</p>

